cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper discusses a randomized controlled trial of video-streaming algorithms for bitrate selection and network prediction, which involves network infrastructure and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of supervised learning, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of machine-learned control schemes, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of classical control, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the variability and heavy-tailed nature of network and algorithm behavior, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
